<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="728" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[2077,2670,1549,1972]" lastBlockId="20.[1462,2667,1978,2524]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2077,2353,1746,1775]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body mean 154 mm (males) and 152 mm (females), tail mean 112 mm (males) and 122 mm (females); weight mean 124 g (males) and 132-5 g (females). Dorsum of Brooke's Squirrel is speckled brown and venter is gray with an orange patch between hindlegs. Tips of ventral hair are whitish. Tail is barred.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1464,2366,2056,2089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[1462,2667,1978,2524]" box="[1464,2366,2056,2089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1464,1575,2056,2089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">Habitat.</emphasis>
