<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="728" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="20.[1462,2667,1978,2524]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1463,1815,2333,2366]" pageId="20" pageNumber="728">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Brooke's Squirrel has relatively a large and stable population in Kinabalu Park. It is probably naturally rare, and as a hill speciesit is not heavily affected by the extensive lowland forest conversions in Borneo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
